  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 14 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 critical, 8 high, 13 medium, 12 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB); plus 11 other bases. 13 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Modlin (WMI/EPMO). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and 9 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 9 others.",
